Blooming 1998 champions


Bolivia Second Level 1998

Copa Simon Bolívar

This tournament is contested by the champions and runners-up of the nine
regional leagues (La Paz, Oruro, Potosí, Cochabamba, Sucre, Tarija,
Pando, Beni, and Santa Cruz).

The winners gain promotion to the national league, the runners-up play off
against the penultimate team of the national league.

First Round [Oct 10 and 17]
Atlético Pompeya (Beni)         3-1 3-0 Vaca Diez (Pando)
Aurora (Cochabamba)             3-0 4-1 Juve Sucrense (Sucre)
Libertad (Santa Cruz)           4-3 2-3 Enrique Happ (Cochabamba)       [3-2 pen]
Municipal (La Paz)             11-1 6-0 Ingenieros (Oruro)
Stormers (Sucre)                2-2 1-1 Mariscal Braun (La Paz)         [4-3 pen]
Municipal Potosí (Potosí)       4-0 2-8 Municipal Braniff (Santa Cruz)
Estudiantes Frontanilla (Oruro) 1-4 1-4 Unión Central (Tarija)
Ciclón (Tarija)                17-1 w/o Atlético Real Villazón (Potosí)
Cobija FC (Cobija)              1-0 1-0 Universitario (Beni)
Enrique Happ (Cochabamba) qualify to second round as best losers.

Second Round [Oct 24 and 31]
Atlético Pompeya (Beni)         7-0 3-0 Cobija FC (Cobija)
Aurora (Cochabamba)             5-3 1-1 Municipal Braniff (Santa Cruz)
Libertad (Santa Cruz)           0-2 1-2 Unión Central (Tarija)
Ciclón (Tarija)                 4-1 2-2 Stormers (Sucre) 
Municipal (La Paz)              3-0 0-1 Enrique Happ (Cochabamba)
Enrique Happ (Cochabamba) qualify to third round as best losers (again!).

Third Round [Nov 7 and 14]
Atlético Pompeya (Beni)         6-1 2-4 Municipal (La Paz)       
Aurora (Cochabamba)             2-1 0-1 Ciclón (Tarija)                 [4-5 pen]
Unión Central (Tarija)          3-1 6-2 Enrique Happ (Cochabamba)
Ciclón (Tarija) qualify to semifinals as best losers.

Semifinals [Nov 21 and 28]
Atlético Pompeya (Beni)         4-1 2-2 Ciclón (Tarija)      
Aurora (Cochabamba)             1-1 3-3 Unión Central (Tarija)          [5-6 pen]

Final [Dec 5 and 12]
Unión Central (Tarija)          1-0 1-1 Atlético Pompeya (Beni)
  [Serrano] []

